<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/93001300/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """Ordinary evaluation
Assignments
40% of your final score will be linked to the results of the assignments (exercises, problems, comments on proposed readings, ...). What will be assessed is the depth, quality, and how it generally compares to the work of your peers.
Final paper and presentation
50% of your final score will be based on an individual paper on a topic of your choice, which you will complete and present to your classmates at the end of the course. The written paper will be evaluated on its depth, quality, and how it compares to the work of your peers. For the presentation, we will assess the clarity, and quality of replies to questions, fitting to time and format.
Class participation
10% of your final score will be linked to your attitude and participation (quality and quantity) in class


Extra evaluation
In the case of failure to pass the ordinary evaluations, the course can be passed in an extra (final) evaluation, typically taking place at the end of the second semester (i.e., by the end of June)."""@es ;
